				<imageExpression><![CDATA["unchecked.png"]]></imageExpression>
			</image>
			<image vAlign="Top">
				<reportElement x="322" y="15" width="10" height="15" uuid="c9ed8c3e-50d7-4a8b-9742-03841ec46d6b">
					<printWhenExpression><![CDATA[$F{ffp2_v3_684_c_v1}.trim().equalsIgnoreCase("No")]]></printWhenExpression>
				</reportElement>
				<imageExpression><![CDATA["checked.png"]]></imageExpression>
			</image>
		</band>
		<band height="135">
			<staticText>
				<reportElement positionType="Float" x="25" y="0" width="545" height="135" uuid="7e1c736d-810d-4880-b97f-351ddfdae828"/>
				<textElement textAlignment="Justified" verticalAlignment="Middle" markup="html">
					<font size="12" pdfFontName="net/sf/jasperreports/fonts/dejavu/DejaVuSerif-Italic.ttf" isPdfEmbedded="true"/>
				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[Depending on the subsequent examination test (e.g. mass spectrometry) additional steps (e.g. generation of peptides) can be required after the removal of the detergent. For the isolation of proteins from a very low number of cells like laser microdissected single cells, different dedicated protein isolation procedures might be needed. For such sensitive procedures it is recommended to follow the latest literature and verify and validate the isolation procedure before use. Partial solubilisation of FFPE tissues can lead to isolation bias and can affect the final assay result.]]></text>
			</staticText>
		</band>
		<band height="52">
			<staticText>
				<reportElement positionType="Float" x="25" y="0" width="545" height="52" uuid="a6b95acb-3f93-425b-ae60-21f6dc2bc75d"/>
				<textElement verticalAlignment="Middle" markup="html">
					<font size="14" isBold="true" pdfFontName="net/sf/jasperreports/fonts/dejavu/DejaVuSerif-Bold.ttf" isPdfEmbedded="true"/>
				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[6.8. Quality assessment of isolated proteins]]></text>
			</staticText>
		</band>
		<band height="110" splitType="Prevent">
			<staticText>
				<reportElement x="25" y="0" width="272" height="110" uuid="97756a90-39cf-4ca0-9eb5-dd1e46b70604"/>
				<textElement verticalAlignment="Top" markup="html">
					<font size="12"/>
				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[para 1) The quantity and quality of protein was checked by generally accepted physical, chemical or biochemical procedures, and/or suitable controls as part of the examination test<br><font color="#004280">should</font><br>]]></text>
			</staticText>
			<staticText>
				<reportElement x="335" y="0" width="22" height="15" uuid="24be0af7-9d5f-4c28-86b2-f404b9045312"/>
				<textElement verticalAlignment="Top" markup="html">
